  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"jump-content\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n            \n\n    \n    \n\n    \u003carticle\u003e\n\n    \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n    \n      \n\n\u003cdiv data-analytics-module=\"{\n    \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Hero Menu\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;How to opt in to holiday package tracking in Gmail\u0026#34;\n  }\"\u003e\n  \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \n            \u003cp\u003eDec 02, 2024\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n          \n            \u003cp data-reading-time-render=\"\"\u003e[[read-time]] min read\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n        \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n        \u003cp\u003e\n          Take the guesswork out of your deliveries.\n        \u003c/p\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n  \u003cdiv data-summary-id=\"ai_summary_1\" data-component=\"uni-ai-generated-summary\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n    \u0026#34;event\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;module_impression\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;ai_summary\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;CTA\u0026#34;\n  }\"\u003e\n          \u003ch2\u003eGeneral summary\u003c/h2\u003e\n          \u003cp\u003eYou can easily track your holiday packages right in Gmail.  Just click \u0026#34;Allow\u0026#34; on the summary card that appears at the top of your emails.  If you haven\u0026#39;t received a summary card yet, you can opt in to package tracking in your Gmail settings.\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n          \u003cp\u003e\u003csmall\u003e\n            Summaries were generated by Google AI. Generative AI is experimental.\n          \u003c/small\u003e\n        \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \n\n    \n      \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cfigure\u003e\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Ink_GmailPackageTracking_2096x118.width-600.format-webp.webp 600w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Ink_GmailPackageTracking_2096x11.width-1200.format-webp.webp 1200w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Ink_GmailPackageTracking_2096x11.width-1600.format-webp.webp 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 600px, 1024px\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Ink_GmailPackageTracking_2096x11.width-1200.format-webp.webp\" fetchpriority=\"high\" alt=\"an illustration of several wrapped presents surrounding a smartphone screen with the phrase \u0026#34;arriving today\u0026#34;\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n\n    \n    \u003cdiv data-reading-time=\"true\" data-component=\"uni-article-body\"\u003e\n\n            \n              \n\n\n\u003cgoogle-read-aloud-player data-analytics-module=\"{\n        \u0026#34;event\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;module_impression\u0026#34;,\n        \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;ai_audio\u0026#34;,\n        \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;How to opt in to holiday package tracking in Gmail\u0026#34;\n    }\" data-date-modified=\"2024-12-02T21:37:41.615370+00:00\" data-progress-bar-style=\"half-wave\" data-api-key=\"AIzaSyBLT6VkYe-x7sWLZI2Ep26-fNkBKgND-Ac\" data-article-style=\"style9\" data-tracking-ids=\"G-HGNBTNCHCQ,G-6NKTLKV14N\" data-voice-list=\"en.ioh-pngnat:Cyan,en.usb-pngnat:Lime\" data-layout-style=\"style1\" data-highlight-mode=\"word-over-paragraph\" data-highlight-text-color=\"#000000\" data-highlight-word-background=\"#8AB4F8\" data-highlight-paragraph-background=\"#D2E3FC\" data-background=\"linear-gradient(180deg, #F1F3F4 0%, #F8F9FA 100%)\" data-foreground-color=\"#202124\" data-font=\"600 16px Google Sans, sans-serif\" data-box-shadow=\"0px 1px 3px 1px rgba(60, 64, 67, 0.15)\"\u003e\n\u003c/google-read-aloud-player\u003e\n\n\n\n\n            \n\n            \n            \n\n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;How to opt in to holiday package tracking in Gmail\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"6h746\"\u003eIt’s no secret that the most wonderful time of the year can also be the busiest. From organizing schedules and travel plans to finding the perfect gift, the holidays can clutter even the most organized inboxes. That’s why this season \u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/inside-google/google-holiday-tips-2024/\"\u003ewe’re highlighting features\u003c/a\u003e to help you simplify the holiday swirl — including this tip on how to avoid email overload and easily keep track of gifts and packages in the mail.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"76ouj\"\u003eWhether you enable package tracking from your new summary cards or want to opt-in before your packages are on their way, we’ll show you how right from your Gmail account.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"3nv26\"\u003eTrack your holiday packages with one click using summary cards\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"f9k85\"\u003eFor years, summary cards in Gmail have put key details about things like events, bills and travel updates right at the top of your emails. Our \u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/products/gmail/new-gmail-summary-cards/\"\u003elatest update\u003c/a\u003e is tailored for the giving (and shipping) season, offering real-time updates on your holiday purchases and a button to quickly opt in to package tracking — which brings the latest shipment information from most major U.S. shipping carriers right into Gmail — with one click.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"cvjn8\"\u003eTo opt in, just click “Allow” on the bottom of the summary card.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n      \u003cdiv data-analytics-module=\"{\n          \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Inline Images\u0026#34;,\n          \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;How to opt in to holiday package tracking in Gmail\u0026#34;\n        }\"\u003e\n  \n\n  \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"two side-by-side smartphones, the one on the left says \u0026#34;Allow\u0026#34; and \u0026#34;not now\u0026#34; as options for package tracking; the one on the right shows a similar view only with a button and the phrase \u0026#34;track package\u0026#34;\" src=\" https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Side-by-side.width-100.format-webp.webp \" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n                \u0026#34;mobile\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Side-by-side.width-500.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;,\n                \u0026#34;desktop\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Side-by-side.width-1000.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;\n              }\"/\u003e\n        \n      \n    \n    \u003c/p\u003e\n    \n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"9ti0m\"\u003ePurchase summary cards are interactive and allow you to opt in to package tracking and view the status of an order. The image on the left shows the opt in button; on the right displays what people will see after package tracking is activated when receiving a package from a supported carrier.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n    \n  \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\n\n  \n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;How to opt in to holiday package tracking in Gmail\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"ga9rn\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/products/gmail/package-tracking/\"\u003eWe first launched package tracking features\u003c/a\u003e in Gmail in 2022, and the updated summary cards make it even simpler to opt in directly from your emails.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"7693m\"\u003eOpt in to package tracking in your Gmail settings\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"15r6j\"\u003ePackage tracking uses your tracking numbers to automatically follow your purchases’ progress and display updates in your emails. But even if you haven’t found the perfect holiday gift, you can still get prepared for the season by opting-in to package tracking right in your Gmail settings. Here’s how to set it up from your Gmail settings:\u003c/p\u003e\u003col\u003e\u003cli data-block-key=\"ad791\"\u003eOpen the Gmail mobile app on your phone, and tap on the menu button (those three horizontal lines in the top left corner).\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-block-key=\"de2d\"\u003eOpen Settings by tapping the Settings bar.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-block-key=\"9h80q\"\u003eIn general settings (or data privacy for iOS users), you’ll find the option to opt in or turn off “Package Tracking.”\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"31tcn\"\u003eYou’ll only need to opt in once for package tracking, and you can opt out at any time.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"erb20\"\u003eWe hope this is helpful as the gifting season kicks off, and we’ll be sharing more \u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/products/maps/plan-your-holiday-drives-with-google-maps-trends/\"\u003etips and tools\u003c/a\u003e this month to help you navigate this time of year. With package tracking, you can spend less time worrying about how to intercept gifts at the door, and more time unwrapping the perfect holiday with your loved ones.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\u003csection data-analytics-module=\"{\n  \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Related Content Tout\u0026#34;,\n  \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Season’s greetings from Google\u0026#34;\n}\"\u003e\n  \u003ca href